==English==

===Verb===
'''[[call]] [[on]]'''
#{{idiom}} To [[visit]] somebody; to pay a [[call]].
#:''I really should '''call on''' my aunt more often.''
#{{idiom}} In a [[classroom]], to [[select]] a [[student]]
#:''He sat there, baffled, hoping nobody would '''call on''' him.''
#{{idiom}} To [[request]] or [[ask]] of somebody; to [[select]] for a [[task]].
#:''The boss '''called on''' him for quite a number of 
#{{idiom}} To [[correct]]; to point out an [[error]] or [[untruth]].
#:''The salesman persisted in quoting a rate higher than was listed, until we '''called him on''' it.''